IADB to Lend Peru $950 Million Through 2012, Andina Agency Says

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-10-20T18:56:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/iadb-to-lend-peru-950-million-through-2012-andina-agency-says.html
The  Inter-American Development Bank 
will lend  Peru  $950 million through 2012, state news agency
 Andina  reported.  The bank will lend Peru $450 million this year and $500
million in 2012, country manager Fernando Montenegro told
Andina. Loans in 2011 will include $300 million for state
projects and $150 million for private industry, according to the
agency.  The lender will also provide Peru with as much as $30
million in donations, Andina said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  